    'user_law' => [
        'title' => '7. User Laws',
        '1' => 'As a user of our platform, you have fundamental rights concerning your personal data, in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and applicable laws. These rights are designed to give you control over the information you entrust to us and ensure complete transparency in its use. We are committed to respecting these rights and facilitating their exercise through simple and accessible means.',
        '2' => 'You have the right to access the personal data we collect and process. This means you can request detailed information about the data we hold, the purposes of its use, the third parties it has been shared with, and the measures taken to ensure its security. We will provide a copy of this data upon request, in a clear and readable format, unless the request is manifestly unfounded or excessive.',
        '3' => 'The right to rectification allows you to request the correction or updating of your personal data if it is inaccurate or incomplete. We encourage you to regularly check the information associated with your account and notify us of any changes to ensure your data remains accurate and up to date. Changes will be made promptly in accordance with our internal procedures.',
        '4' => 'You also have the right to request the deletion of your personal data, also known as the "right to be forgotten." This allows you to request the removal of your information when it is no longer needed for the purposes for which it was collected or when you withdraw your consent. We will delete your data within a reasonable timeframe unless its retention is required by a legal obligation or to respond to an ongoing dispute.',
        '5' => 'The right to restriction of processing allows you to temporarily or permanently limit the use of your data in certain circumstances. For example, if you contest the accuracy of your information or object to its processing, you can request that its use be suspended until the situation is resolved. During this period, your data will be retained but not actively used.',
        '6' => 'You also have the right to data portability, which allows you to receive the personal information you have provided to us in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format. This right also enables you to transfer this data to another controller, where technically feasible, to facilitate a transition to another service or provider.',
        '7' => 'The right to object allows you to refuse the processing of your personal data in certain circumstances, particularly if this processing is based on our legitimate interest or for marketing purposes. If you exercise this right, we will cease using your data for these purposes unless we can demonstrate compelling legitimate grounds justifying the continuation of processing.',
        '8' => 'To exercise any of these rights, you can contact us at any time using the contact details provided in this policy. We will respond to your requests within the legally required timeframes, usually within one month, and will inform you of the progress or any reasons justifying an extension of this period. We may request additional information to verify your identity before processing your request, to protect your data from unauthorized access.',
        '9' => 'We are committed to respecting your rights and providing the necessary information to exercise them fully. If you believe your rights have not been respected or that your data has been processed inappropriately, you have the right to file a complaint with the competent data protection authority in your jurisdiction. However, we encourage you to contact us first to resolve any issues amicably and quickly.',
